Upon completion of the course, students should be able to:

* understand the principles of engineering geology and appreciate the role of engineering geologists;
* understand the methods of desk study, ground investigation and engineering geological assessment;
* conduct soil and rock description and classification for engineering purposes, as well as rock joint surveys; and
* appreciate the application of engineering geology principles in various civil engineering works through selected case histories from Hong Kong.

